{
  "stem": "8569.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And the young man fell on her and sunk his teeth right into it, because what happened was he thought it was food.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And what was happening is that the Jewish police was running after the youngsters that were assaulting people, and ripping their possessions off their hands, and confiscating it.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So they have learned when they took something, immediately put it in their mouth so that it won't be taken away from them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Also the transports were getting more and more often.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We used to have my aunt, my father's sister living with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And like many other people, because they didn't know what tomorrow will bring, people were walking around with knapsacks where they kept all of their most precious possessions in case they're going to be taken away.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "At least they will have it with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And she was taken with her knapsack one day off the street, and we never saw her again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "At that time, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was telling you that my father was registered in making this wooden frame.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And he got an apartment which was vacated, an empty apartment to have his workshop in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And my father told my sister and me to start taking the wooden frames and put it there is to make it look occupied.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And one day, my sister and I were walking.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "It was just across the street from where we were, and there was a selection.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Selection means-- not a selection.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "It was a run.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "What it meant was that the streets were cordoned off by the SS, the Polish police, and the Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the Germans were running on the streets and in the buildings telling people to get out.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
